Las Vegas, NV 

A man believed to be casing homes near the southwest valley is fighting for his life after being shot by a homeowner. Police found the victim suffering from two gunshot wounds around 6:30 p.m. at the intersection of Remuda and Desert Inn. 

The man who fired the shots told police he had been asked by a neighbor to check out his home, concerned people were breaking in. A confrontation ensued between the homeowner and the suspect escalating to the homeowner shooting the suspect.</content> 
